  "body": "As discussed with @aturon, this PR removes the `Send` bound from `std::error::Error`, allowing us to implement `Error` for error types containing non-`Send` types. Current examples include `PoisonError` and `TryLockError` from `std::sync` which contain a Guard that we don't want sent between tasks.\n\n[breaking-change]\n",
